<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 01:00:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>国家气候报告中发现废水甲烷缺口</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/wastewater-methane-gaps-found-in-national-climate-reports</link><description>“如果你不知道自己到底有多少排放量，那么就很难制定有效的政策或技术或方法来减少排放，”Z. Jason Ren 博士说。 [ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/wastewater-methane-gaps-found-in-national-climate-reports.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 01:00:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/wastewater-methane-gaps-found-in-national-climate-reports</guid></item><item><title>工程免疫疗法可以帮助对抗大脑衰老</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/engineered-immune-therapy-could-help-fight-brain-aging</link><description>斯坦福大学的研究人员设计了免疫蛋白白细胞介素 10 (IL-10) 的改良版本，仅保留其抗炎特性，同时消除其促炎特性。当注射到老年小鼠体内时，这种修饰过的蛋白质会刺激新神经元的生长，并提高记忆和学习任务的表现，例如迷宫导航和物体识别。这项发表在《免疫》杂志上的研究表明，与年龄相关的认知能力下降与大脑中耗尽的 T 淋巴细胞的积累、慢性炎症和小胶质细胞功能受损有关，所有这些都会减少神经发生。研究结果表明，选择性调节免疫信号可以为治疗神经退行性疾病开辟新途径。该团队计划进一步研究该蛋白质的机制，并探索更精确地针对特定细胞类型的方法，以尽量减少潜在的副作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/engineered-immune-therapy-could-help-fight-brain-aging2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:45:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/engineered-immune-therapy-could-help-fight-brain-aging</guid></item><item><title>决定魔法的难以承受的难度</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/the-unbearable-hardness-of-deciding-about-magic</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:30:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/the-unbearable-hardness-of-deciding-about-magic</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，食癌细菌可能有助于治疗难以治疗的肿瘤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/cancer-eating-bacteria-may-help-with-hard-to-treat-tumors-new-research-shows</link><description>我们在本周的 InnovationRx 版中研究了更便宜的药物替代品，例如 Keytruda、诺和诺德用于生产下一代 Wegovy 药丸的 GLP-1 协议等。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cancer-eating-bacteria-may-help-with-hard-to-treat-tumors-new-research-shows.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:15:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/cancer-eating-bacteria-may-help-with-hard-to-treat-tumors-new-research-shows</guid></item><item><title>这种基因开关有助于免疫细胞保护您的器官</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/this-genetic-switch-helps-immune-cells-protect-your-organs</link><description>单个基因“开关”可能是身体清洁工如何成长并保持我们的器官顺利运转的秘密。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/this-genetic-switch-helps-immune-cells-protect-your-organs.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:00:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/this-genetic-switch-helps-immune-cells-protect-your-organs</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局宣布改变其登月计划</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nasa-announces-change-to-its-moon-landing-plans</link><description>在将宇航员送上月球之前，它正在为其阿尔忒弥斯计划增加一项额外的任务。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nasa-announces-change-to-its-moon-landing-plans.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 23:45:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nasa-announces-change-to-its-moon-landing-plans</guid></item><item><title>遗传性疾病并不像我们想象的那样起作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/inherited-diseases-dont-work-like-we-thought-they-did</link><description>仅由一个基因突变引发的“单基因”疾病实际上可能比科学家想象的更复杂。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/inherited-diseases-dont-work-like-we-thought-they-did.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 23:30:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/inherited-diseases-dont-work-like-we-thought-th